Supposedly when all things are implemented Player made will be better than anything dropped. Right now there is nothing better than the sdropped items in Spind. <br>
<br>
No matter how trivial items are some people are always going to have a trinket driven mentality. Especially if those items have varying difficulties in obtainability. <br>
<br>
In DAoC they have done away with alot of this. Anyone can get any item as long as you can kill the mobs it drops on or have attained the one time drop level for the item.<br>
<br>
Items mean so much in EQ that I had people I had never met send me tells asking me about certain items I was st on the server with, RBB, Rakusha cloak, Fungi covered tunic, There is nothing like this is DAoC ( so far)<br>
<br>
<br>
Chuk,<br>
<br>
There is No comparison that can be made in EQ and DAoC camping. the way they each do exp is completely different.<br>
<br>
In EQ you can kill the same mobs 24/7 365 and they will always be worth the same amount of exp as when you started. <br>
<br>
In DAoC you start killing a camp of mobs and the exp you get slowly gets smaller and smaller till all the bonus is gone and your just getting baseline exp. This is how DAoC rewards you for moving to other spots.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
DAoC is IMO not a great game, maybe its a good game waiting to happen. If they make the RVR actually have some meaning add some higher level content between Vanern-Spind and the insanely hard Raumarik, Then it might be good. Right now its just somthing to do between now and SB beta which will hopefully be a good game or more.<br>
