<br>
Depends entirely on your class.<br>
<br>
In his high teens, my Theurgist was still wearing mostly tattered woolen crap that had dropped back at 1st level off of imps.  It was 15 odd levels grey to him and had all the protective value of damp mold, but since he didn't get hit, it really didn't matter...  It was 20 levels before someone in my guild told me what focus staves did.  I'd never bothered to get one.  And I'd done fine, soloing reds and oranges like any good Theurgist.  (Apparently stuff can't go below 0% Condition, in case anyone was wondering.  Ahem.  I didn't know what Smiths were for either...)<br>
<br>
By 10th level, my Hunter was SUCKING and I couldn't tell why.  Finally I begrudgingly learned Fletching so I could use some better arrows than the stuff my guild trainer had been handing out for free (the worst arrows in the game) and upgraded my armor from that tattered crap I'd been wearing for 9 levels, and omigod did things change.  Suddenly mobs were dying before they got to me, doing less than maximum damage on every hit (and even missing sometimes) and with my spiffy new player-made Spear (which was 10% better than vendor crap), I was ripping stuff apart.<br>
<br>
If you absolutely *despise* going out and questing or crafting good gear for your character (monster dropped gear is third-rate in quality), play something that doesn't need gear.<br>
